ZH: 我昨天晚上听写了一篇英语短文。

EN: I listened to and wrote down an English passage last night.

ZH: 她每天晚上都要花时间听写生词。

EN: She spends time listening to and writing down new vocabulary every night.

ZH: 我们的老师每周给我们安排听写任务。

EN: Our teacher assigns us dictation tasks every week.

ZH: 他宁愿听写也不愿意背诵。

EN: He prefers listening to dictation rather than memorizing.

ZH: 学生们需要做听写来巩固学过的知识。

EN: Students need to do dictation to solidify the knowledge they have learned.

ZH: 听写对提高听力和拼写能力很有帮助。

EN: Dictation is very helpful for improving listening and spelling skills.

ZH: 他常常做听写以加深对中文的理解。

EN: He often does dictation to deepen his understanding of Chinese.

ZH: 我们要交听写的本子给老师检查。

EN: We have to hand in our dictation notebooks to the teacher for inspection.

ZH: 听写是检验学生理解能力的好方法。

EN: Dictation is a good way to test students' comprehension.

ZH: 我觉得听写是学习外语的有效方法之一。

EN: I think dictation is one of the effective ways to learn a foreign language.

ZH: 每周五我们都要做中文听写。

EN: We have Chinese dictation every Friday.

ZH: 她很认真地完成了听写任务。

EN: She completed the dictation task very seriously.

ZH: 她经常让孩子们做听写练习。

EN: She often makes the children do dictation exercises.

ZH: 这个单词我在听写中经常拼错。

EN: I often spell this word wrong in dictation.

ZH: 为了做到听写不出错，我要多加练习。

EN: In order to avoid mistakes in dictation, I need to practice more.

ZH: 我们班的听写难度逐渐增加了。

EN: The difficulty of our dictation in class is increasing gradually.

ZH: 她通过听写提高了自己的语文水平。

EN: She improved her Chinese level through dictation.
